1. Vožnja bicikla je odlična fizička aktivnost. (*vožnja*, subject of the sentence) (Riding a bicycle is a great physical activity.)
2. Svakodnevna vožnja autobusom može biti naporna. (*vožnja*, modifier of the noun "autobusom") (Daily bus ride can be exhausting.)
3. Za vozače kamiona, vožnja je često teška i naporna. (*vožnja*, subject of the sentence) (For truck drivers, driving is often difficult and exhausting.)
4. Vožnju možemo produžiti za još nekoliko kilometara. (*vožnju*, object of the verb "produžiti") (We can extend the ride for a few more kilometers.)
5. Autobuska linija ima redovne vožnje do centra grada. (*vožnje*, noun in plural form, object of the preposition "do") (The bus line has regular rides to the city center.)
6. Kako si prošao na vožnji? (*vožnji*, object of the preposition "na") (How was your driving experience?)
7. Vožnja je obustavljena zbog loših vremenskih uslova. (*vožnja*, subject of the sentence) (The ride is suspended due to bad weather conditions.)
8. Svi putnici moraju da stave pojas tokom vožnje. (*vožnje*, genitive case, modifying the noun "pojas") (All passengers must fasten their seat belts during the ride.)
9. Vozio sam brzo tokom cele vožnje. (*vožnje*, genitive case, modifying the noun "cele") (I drove fast throughout the entire ride.)
10. Železnička stanica je mesto polaska vožnje. (*vožnje*, genitive case, modifying the noun "polaska") (The train station is the place of departure for the ride.)